    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-05-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-07-02T19:40:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Instructs the Assistant Secretary of Energy for Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy to establish an advisory committee to: (1) advise the Department of Energy on energy efficiency and renewable energy finance and investment issues; and (2) assist the energy community in identifying ways of lowering costs and increasing investments in energy efficiency and renewable energy technologies.</p> <p>Requires committee membership to represent: (1) providers of seed capital; (2) venture capitalists; (3) private equity sources; (4) investment banking corporate finance; (5) investment banking mergers and acquisitions; (6) equity capital markets; (7) debt capital markets; (8) research analysts; (9) sales and trading; (10) commercial lenders; and (11) residential lenders.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To provide for the establishment of an energy efficiency and renewable energy finance and investment advisory committee.</title>
